==Old English==

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'bera/

===Etymology===
From the West Germanic ''*beran-'', from Indo-European ''*bher-'' (''brown animal'').  Cognate with the Old High German ''[[bero]]'' (and German ''[[Bär]]''), Middle Dutch ''bere'' (and Dutch ''[[beer]]''), Old Norse ''ber'' (''bear'').  A North Germanic variant, ''*bernu-'', gave Old Norse {{Latinx|[[bjǫrn]]}} (cf. Swedish ''[[björn]]'').  The Proto-Indo-European root is also the source of the Common Slavic *''[[brlog]]'' (and thence, Russian [[берлога]], ''den'').

===Noun===
'''bera''' ''m'' (pl. ''beran'')

# [[bear]]

[[Category:Old English nouns]]

